    scholarsSaid: [
      { scholar: "Ibn al-Qayyim", source: "Al-Fawa'id", text: "Whoever knows the worth of the akhira relative to the dunya will realize he has sold what is priceless for what is worthless — unless he orients the dunya toward the akhira." },
      { scholar: "Al-Hasan al-Basri", text: "Make your work for this world proportional to how long you will stay in it, and your work for the akhira proportional to how long you will stay in it." },
      { scholar: "Ibn Ata Allah al-Iskandari", source: "Al-Hikam", text: "He made the akhira a home for His believing servants not because it is more worthy of them, but because He knew that the dunya was too narrow to contain what He wanted to bestow upon them." },
    ],
    hadith: [
      { text: "The smart person is one who holds their self to account and works for what comes after death; and the weak person is one who follows their desires and then hopes in Allah.", source: "Sunan al-Tirmidhi — Hasan" },
      { text: "Paradise is surrounded by hardships, and the Fire is surrounded by pleasures.", source: "Sahih Muslim" },
    ],
    acrossTransitions: "The akhira is not merely an eschatological doctrine — it is a way of seeing everything else. The Quran's consistent pairing of dunya and akhira creates a bifocal vision: every scene in this life is simultaneously itself and a doorway to its ultimate meaning.\n\nIn the legal tradition, the akhira functions as the ultimate sanction. Where human law cannot reach — the private injustice, the unwitnessed betrayal — the akhira holds the account. This is why Islamic ethics does not ultimately depend on enforcement; it depends on the internalized reality of divine witnessing and final judgment.\n\nIn Sufi thought, the akhira transforms into an experiential category: the mystic seeks to enter the reality of the akhira now — to die before death, to experience the meeting with Allah within this life through the annihilation of the ego. The Quranic injunction to 'strive toward Allah a true striving' (22:78) becomes the project of the entire spiritual path.",
