        note: "The Quran describes itself as mubarak — blessed. This is not merely a claim to authority; it is a promise of function. A blessed book is one whose engagement yields more than the time and effort invested — understanding deepens, character transforms, hearts soften. The barakah of the Quran is experienced in the reading.",
